function aliceWins(piles) {
    let xorSum = 0;
    for (let pile of piles) {
        xorSum ^= pile;
    }
    return xorSum !== 0;
}
```


    The game is actually a variant of Nim game. The optimal strategy is that both players keep reducing piles to ensure that the bitwise XOR of all piles remains 0. After each player's turn, if the bitwise XOR of all piles is 0, the player wins if there are no piles with stones left; otherwise, the player loses.

To determine if Alice wins, we first calculate the bitwise XOR of all the piles' sizes. If the bitwise XOR is not 0, Alice can win by making a move that changes the XOR to 0. Otherwise, Alice will lose since any move she makes will give Bob a chance to make XOR 0 afterward.

So the algorithm is simply to calculate the XOR of all piles and compare the final result to 0.

